Method Detail

CoInitialize

public static void CoInitialize()
                         throws COMException
Initializes the COM library for use by the calling thread and set the thread's concurrency model to a COINIT.APARTMENTTHREADED thread.

Multithreaded applications should call CoInitialize(COINIT) instead.

Throws:
COMException - if unable to initialize the COM library successfully.

CoInitialize

public static void CoInitialize(COINIT coinit)
                         throws COMException
Initializes the COM library for use by the calling thread, sets the thread's concurrency model to coinit, and creates a new apartment for the thread if one is required.

This method should be used instead of CoInitialize() in multithreaded applications, with a COINIT.MULTITHREADED parameter.

Parameters:
coinit - the threads concurrency model.
Throws:
COMException - if unable to initialize the COM library successfully.
java.lang.NullPointerException - if coinit is null.
